{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17516423","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17516423"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T13:42:19+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T13:42:19+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12617"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"12617","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/12617"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.18,0.54,0.23,0.03,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"5103"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"111320"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"5103","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/5103"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12617"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"93448"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"10"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"1306"},{"type":"tags","id":"2355"},{"type":"tags","id":"2936"},{"type":"tags","id":"3056"},{"type":"tags","id":"9641"},{"type":"tags","id":"12920"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"8538"},{"type":"contributions","id":"8642"},{"type":"contributions","id":"45207"},{"type":"contributions","id":"49016"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"111320","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/111320"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 52-year-old man presents to his General Practitioner wanting to discuss his cannabis use. He reports using cannabis daily for the past year to help with anxiety and insomnia. His past medical history includes diabetes, for which he takes metformin, and hypertension managed with lisinopril. He does not smoke tobacco and drinks four glasses of wine a day.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most commonly associated long-term consequence of cannabis use that this patient should be counselled about?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Cardiac arrhythmias","Cognitive impairment","Chronic obstructive pulmonary disease","Liver cirrhosis","Chronic renal failure"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EChronic cannabis use has been associated with \u003Cstrong\u003Ecognitive impairment\u003C/strong\u003E, including deficits in attention, memory, executive functioning and verbal fluency. Cognitive impairment can occur regardless of the age at which cannabis use begins, though executive function in particular is more affected when use starts in adolescence. Whilst some improvement may be seen following sustained abstinence, cognitive impairment can persist after cessation of cannabis use and is more likely with heavy, chronic use.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAlthough this patient has risk factors for developing \u003Cstrong\u003Ecardiac arrhythmias,\u003C/strong\u003E specifically heavy smoking and alcohol use, chronic cannabis use has not been consistently linked to a higher risk of cardiac arrhythmias.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EChronic Obstructive Pulmonary Disease (COPD)\u003C/strong\u003E is not the correct option because cannabis smoking independent to cigarette smoking has not been proven to be a causative factor for COPD. Patients who smoke both tobacco and marijuana are at increased risk of respiratory symptoms than tobacco smokers only, however this patient does not smoke tobacco.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe patient currently exceeds the recommended intake of alcohol for Australians, which does put him at risk of \u003Cstrong\u003Eliver cirrhosis\u003C/strong\u003E. This is not the correct option, however, as there is no conclusive evidence that cannabis use increases the risk of liver cirrhosis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhilst this patient is at risk of \u003Cstrong\u003Erenal failure\u003C/strong\u003E due to his diabetes and hypertension, cannabis use has not been shown to increase this risk.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Chronic cannabis use has been associated with cognitive impairment.","Cannabis use can exacerbate existing mental health conditions such as anxiety and insomnia."],"references":["Crean R, Crane N, Mason B. An Evidence Based Review of Acute and Long-Term Effects of Cannabis Use on Executive Cognitive Functions. J Addict Med. [Internet]. 2011 Mar 1 [cited 2023 Mar 28]; 5(1): 1\u20138. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3037578/.","Tan WC, Lo C, Jong A, Xing L, Fitzgerald MJ, Vollmer WM, Buist SA, Sin DD; Vancouver Burden of Obstructive Lung Disease (BOLD) Research Group. Marijuana and chronic obstructive lung disease: a population-based study. CMAJ. 2009 Apr 14;180(8):814-20. Available at: https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC2665947/","Tashkin D. Does smoking marijuana increase the risk of chronic obstructive pulmonary disease? CMAJ.  [Internet]. 2009 Apr 14 [cited 2023 Mar 28]; 180(8): 797\u2013798. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2665954/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"93448"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12617"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"93448","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/93448"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-08-12T13:33:46+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-08-12T13:35:28+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"5103"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"111320"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"10","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/10"},"attr